<h2>Product Description</h2>
Awning windows by Solar Innovations, Inc. provide exceptional performance for an economical price. This type of window hinges at the top of the frame, allowing the bottom to be pushed outward. There is a lock on the interior, which can be unlocked and the window will push to the outside. Screens can be applied on the interior so you can still enjoy a fresh breeze of air without the intrusion of insects.

All awning windows manufactured by Solar Innovations, Inc. are constructed out of durable aluminum. There are six standard finishes and two anodized finishes available, along with any custom color your job may require. The look of a wood window is available with the use of a veneer applied to the frame. Various wood species are available, including mahogany, pine, birch, and Douglas fir.

If you already have awning windows, but they are in some way damaged, Solar Innovations, Inc. offers repair services. An install team can come to the job site and are typically able to repair the awning window. Awning window replacement is also an option if the windows are beyond repair[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37247" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Awning-Crank.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Crank Operation</h2>
Awning windows are available with a crank operator. Instead of having to manually push open the window, the crank can be utilized to open the unit. The screen is mounted on the interior of the window, allowing the breeze to enter but preventing insects from entering. This model comes with a limiter, which allows the window to open without exceeding its operable limits.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="size-full wp-image-37240 alignnone" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Awning-InSystem.png" alt="awning windows" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>In-System Applications</h2>
Awning windows are a popular choice for in-system windows in greenhouses, conservatories, sunrooms, and other Glass Structures. These windows operate like vents, naturally allowing for air circulation. Cool air can enter through windows place lower on the structure, while hot air escapes through awning windows placed at the ridge of the structure.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-37253" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Awning-Misc.png" alt="" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Mulled Capabilities</h2>
With our Mulled Window System, awning windows can be used in conjunction with multiple other operable window &amp; door choices. No additional framing is required when mulling together multiple windows and doors, allowing for consistent sightlines and a clean appearance.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36904 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/screen-option-icon.png" alt="" width="73" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Screen Options</h2>
Screen options are available on a wide variety of our door and window products. These screen options help keep the pests at bay while still allowing you to view the outdoors.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36902 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/hardware-icon.png" alt="" width="86" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Vertical Integration</h2>
Solar manufactures not only its products but also many of the components it uses for the hardware. This allows us to better control lead times to help server our customers better.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36901 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/glass-options-icon.png" alt="" width="65" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Glass Variety</h2>
Solar Innovations has top of the line glazing solutions which include laminated, dual glazed, triple glazed, &amp; marine glazed options just to name a few.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36897 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/made-in-usa-icon.png" alt="" width="159" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Made in America</h2>
All our products are designed and manufactured in the United States at our state-of-the-art facility in Pine Grove, PA.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Operation</h2>
<img class="size-full wp-image-37302 alignleft" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Awning-Operation.gif" alt="" width="232" height="295" />
Awning windows are hinged at the top and open outward from the bottom, similar to eave vents on a structure.

Allowing for additional ventilation without the risk of precipitation falling into the room, awning windows are a popular choice for both in-system and out-of-system applications.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<code>[video_lightbox_youtube video_id="td6ZVhL6m10" width="679" height="403" anchor="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Window-Video.png"  alt="Window Systems"]</code>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]";s:10:"post_title";s:14:"Awning Windows";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:14:"awning-windows";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-08-29 19:57:04";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-08-29 19:57:04";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:38103;s:4:"guid";s:42:"http://solarinnovations.com/?page_id=36460";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:4:"page";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}